Description: Head of a large bronze mummy-case in the form of a cat, hollow-cast with incised decoration, both ears pierced, eyes originally inlaid, hole in the back of the head.
Curator's comments: Bourriau, J, JEA Vol.62, 1976, p. 147, pl. XXVII,2.
Condition: fair (incomplete and back of head damaged)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Christabel Mary McLaren, Lady Aberconway
